Energy management refers to the planning and operation of energy production and energy consumption units along with energy distribution and storage. Objectives include climate protection, cost savings and resource conservation, while the users possess permanent access to the energy they need. The management is connected closely to production management, and environmental management, among established business functions.

The increase in the mandatory regulations and policies across the globe acts as one of the major factors driving the growth of energy management at workplace market. The rise in awareness about the energy management systems owing to various benefits associated with it, and growing demand and usage of energy management systems because of growth of well-organized healthcare and retail sector accelerate the market growth. The increase in energy consumption of various equipment, machinery along with tools contributing towards significant energy consumption of the plant, and rise in inclination towards corporate responsibility and brand image further influence the market. Additionally, price volatility, urbanization and digitization, rise in awareness about carbon footprint management and high focus on towards corporate responsibility and brand image positively affect the energy management at workplace market. Furthermore, integration of energy management systems with smart devices, and exemption from energy and carbon tax policies for the commercial and industrial sector extend profitable opportunities to the market players in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028.

On the other hand, high initial cost of deployment and lack of financial resources are expected to obstruct the market growth. Long period of return on investment for energy-intensive industries and non-standardized guidelines are projected to challenge the energy management at workplace market in the forecast period of 2021-2028.

